  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-2 mb-8">
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="cursor-pointer font-medium text-gray-900 py-2">What is included in an SEO audit for a Swansea business?</summary>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-2">A full SEO audit covers five areas: technical health (site speed, crawlability, indexation, HTTPS), on-page optimisation (titles, meta descriptions, headings, content quality), off-page analysis (backlink profile, referring domains, toxic links), local SEO (Google Business Profile, citations, local schema), and competitor analysis. You receive a prioritised report with specific recommendations ranked by impact.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="cursor-pointer font-medium text-gray-900 py-2">How long does an SEO audit take?</summary>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-2">A standard audit for a Swansea business website with up to 100 pages takes 5 to 7 working days. Larger sites with hundreds or thousands of pages, such as e-commerce stores or directories, may take up to two weeks. You receive the full written report plus a 30-minute walkthrough call to discuss findings and priorities.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="cursor-pointer font-medium text-gray-900 py-2">How much does an SEO audit cost in Swansea?</summary>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-2">SEO audit pricing starts from £500 for small business websites. The exact cost depends on the number of pages, complexity of your CMS, and whether you need competitor analysis included. Visit our <a href="/seo-pricing-swansea/" class="text-brand hover:underline">pricing page</a> for full details or request a custom quote for your Swansea business.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="cursor-pointer font-medium text-gray-900 py-2">What is the difference between a free SEO audit and a paid audit?</summary>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-2">The free audit is an automated health check covering headline issues like site speed, mobile usability, broken links, and basic on-page factors. The paid audit is a manual, in-depth analysis conducted by an SEO specialist covering all five audit pillars with a detailed written report, spreadsheet of issues, and a strategy call. The paid audit finds issues that automated tools miss.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="cursor-pointer font-medium text-gray-900 py-2">Will the audit fix my website or just identify problems?</summary>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-2">The audit identifies and prioritises problems but does not include implementation. We provide clear, actionable recommendations that your developer or team can follow. If you want us to implement the fixes, we offer that as a separate service or as part of an ongoing SEO retainer. Many Swansea businesses choose to start with the audit and then move to a monthly retainer for implementation.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="cursor-pointer font-medium text-gray-900 py-2">How often should a Swansea business run an SEO audit?</summary>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-2">We recommend a comprehensive audit every 12 months at minimum, with lighter quarterly reviews in between. You should also run an audit after any major website change such as a redesign, CMS migration, or domain move. If your rankings suddenly drop, an audit is the fastest way to identify whether a technical issue or Google algorithm update is the cause.</p>
    </details>
  </div>

